 of Commons – equipping it to fulfil its important role as a cornerstone of our democracy – or see it fade into irrelevance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoliticianszGreat BritainxPublic opinion. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh  aBoris Johnson.  aHouse of Commons.  aMembers of Parliament.  acoronavirus.  alegislation.  aliberal democracy.  aparliament.  aparliamentary procedure.  aparliamentary reform.  arepresentation.  arestoration and renewal.  ascrutiny.1 aWhite, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615670940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526156709423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526156709/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles